{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":98364,"duration_api_ms":75110,"num_turns":27,"result":"The fix has been successfully applied. The change is exactly as in PR #11023:\n\n**Summary of the fix:**\n- **File:** `dask/dataframe/groupby.py`\n- **Function:** `_value_counts_aggregate`\n- **Change:** Added a check for empty `data` dictionary after the groupby comprehension. When a branch (partition) exists with only NaN values, the `data` dict would be empty, causing `pd.concat` to fail. The fix creates an empty Series with the appropriate index structure to avoid the failure.\n\nThis is a minimal, targeted fix that handles the edge case where all values in a partition are NaN, which would previously cause `value_counts` to raise an error.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"8b8b2c53-37cf-429b-b611-588e1da85d72","total_cost_usd":0.51789465,"usage":{"input_tokens":137345,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1039,"cache_read_input_tokens":91928,"output_tokens":4959,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"cache_deleted_input_tokens":0,"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed":{"inputTokens":137345,"outputTokens":4959,"cacheReadInputTokens":91928,"cacheCreationInputTokens":1039,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.51789465,"contextWindow":196000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"000e3e94-3459-455f-a753-9b837ab78512"}
